{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsYjiMLq3qjsf6qgUh3s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is deployed and verified. Summary:\n\n**Deployed in `elasticsearch` namespace (all native K8s resources, no operators/CRDs):**\n- `ConfigMap/es-config` — `elasticsearch.yml` with security enabled, HTTPS on the transport+HTTP layers using the existing `es-http-tls` secret (transport uses `verification_mode: certificate` so the cert, which is scoped for the `es-http` service name, works for inter-node auth too)\n- `Service/es-transport` (headless, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) — governs the StatefulSet and enables discovery; this was the key fix, since headless services normally only publish endpoints for Ready pods, creating a deadlock where nodes can't discover peers to form a cluster before becoming Ready\n- `Service/es-http` (ClusterIP, port 9200) — matches the cert's CN/SAN (`es-http`, `*.elasticsearch.svc[.cluster.local]`)\n- `StatefulSet/es-cluster` (3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` to avoid ordered-readiness deadlock), `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` sourced from the `elastic-password` secret to bootstrap the built-in `elastic` user\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/es-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2` to preserve quorum during voluntary disruptions\n\n**Verified:**\n- All 3 pods Ready, cluster status `green`, 3/3 nodes and data nodes\n- HTTPS reachable through `es-http` service from another pod\n- Write (index), read (get by ID), and search all succeeded; cleaned up the test index afterward"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1274,"cache_read_input_tokens":95944,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1274},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2be9da49-6c7a-4500-bc